<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section section--cream">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="section-heading reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Common Questions</span>
      <h2>Assisted Living — FAQs</h2>
    </div>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Who is assisted living designed for?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Assisted living is for seniors who want to maintain as much independence as possible while receiving support with some activities of daily living: bathing, dressing, grooming, medication management, or mobility. If managing a private home has become difficult but a nursing home feels like too much, assisted living is typically the right fit.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">What makes Azalea Estates different from a personal care home?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">We hold an Assisted Living License from the State of Georgia, a more rigorous designation than a Personal Care Home. This means our staffing ratios, nursing oversight, care plan requirements, and state inspections are held to a higher standard. We are one of only two licensed assisted living providers in Fayette County.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">What&rsquo;s included in the monthly rate?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">The monthly rate covers your private suite, all utilities and cable (except phone), full building WiFi, three daily chef-prepared meals, weekly housekeeping and linen service, emergency response systems, and access to all wellness, activity, and community amenities. Personal care services are added in flexible tiers based on assessed needs.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Can you help with long-term care insurance?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Yes. Our admissions team is experienced in helping residents apply and submit monthly claim forms for long-term care insurance. Many residents have a substantial portion of their costs covered through their policies. We are happy to help you understand your coverage and manage the process.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Are assisted living fees tax deductible?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Under many circumstances, yes. Medical expenses for assisted living care, including the personal care portion of the monthly fee, may qualify as deductible. We recommend consulting with your accountant or tax advisor to confirm what applies to your specific situation. Our team can share general guidance to bring to that conversation.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">How is the care plan developed?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Before move-in, our Resident Care Director meets with the prospective resident, their family, and their physician to complete a care assessment. We build an individualized care plan from that assessment, reviewed and updated regularly as needs evolve. Family members are included in every meaningful update.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

